{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775854034770,"sessionID":"ses_286db11edffe7MbduyFHkzy6Ym","part":{"id":"prt_d79251bfb001ONH9tv75VtJvWA","messageID":"msg_d7924f986001dNx3wY2YYGQ7xV","sessionID":"ses_286db11edffe7MbduyFHkzy6Ym","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_d8fd44c7194649debe9f344f","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AR-022: CLI `publish` Command — Technical Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `publish` command deploys a packaged and built agent to either an AgentCube AgentRuntime Custom Resource or standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service. It handles image preparation, provider-specific deployment, metadata updates, and readiness verification.\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Command Interface\n\n### Typer Command Signature\n\n```python\ndef publish(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n    image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n    image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n    image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n    region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n    node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n    replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n    namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n### CLI Flow\n\n1. Parse and validate all options\n2. Resolve `workspace` to absolute `Path`\n3. Initialize `PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)`\n4. Build options dict from CLI parameters\n5. Call `runtime.publish(workspace_path, **options)`\n6. Display success output with deployment details\n7. Handle errors via `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)`\n\n---\n\n## PublishRuntime Implementation\n\n### Class Structure\n\n**File:** `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n\n```python\nclass PublishRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.provider = provider\n        self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n        self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n```\n\n### Core Method: `publish()`\n\n**Signature:**\n```python\ndef publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n```\n\n**Flow:**\n1. Validate workspace path exists and is directory\n2. Load metadata from workspace (`agent_metadata.yaml` with fallbacks)\n3. Apply CLI option overrides to metadata\n4. Validate publish prerequisites based on provider\n5. Prepare image for publishing (local build or cloud image)\n6. Route to provider-specific publish method:\n   - `provider=\"agentcube\"` → `_publish_cr_to_k8s()`\n   - `provider=\"k8s\"` → `_publish_k8s()`\n7. Update publish metadata with deployment results\n8. Return deployment result dict\n\n**Options dict keys:**\n- `version`, `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password`\n- `description`, `region`, `cloud_provider`\n- `node_port`, `replicas`, `namespace`\n\n### Image Preparation\n\n#### `_prepare_image_for_publishing()`\n\n```python\ndef _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n```\n\n**Decision logic:**\n- If `metadata.build_mode == \"local\"`:\n  - Requires `image_url` from CLI options\n  - Calls `_prepare_local_image()` to build and push via Docker\n- If `metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\"`:\n  - Calls `_prepare_cloud_image()` to resolve cloud image reference\n- Returns final image URL string\n\n#### `_prepare_local_image()`\n\n**Flow:**\n1. Validate Docker availability via `docker_service.check_docker_available()`\n2. If `image_url` not provided, raise `ValueError(\"Image URL is required for local build mode\")`\n3. Build image tag from metadata (agent_name + version or \"latest\")\n4. If credentials provided (`image_username`, `image_password`):\n   - Login to registry via `docker_service._docker_login_sdk()`\n5. Push image via `docker_service.push_image()`\n6. Return pushed image URL\n\n#### `_prepare_cloud_image()`\n\n**Flow:**\n1. Resolve cloud image URL from metadata or options\n2. Validate image URL format\n3. Return cloud image URL (no local Docker operations)\n\n### AgentCube Provider: `_publish_cr_to_k8s()`\n\n```python\ndef _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n```\n\n**Prerequisites validation:**\n- `metadata.router_url` must be set\n- `metadata.workload_manager_url` must be set\n- Raise `ValueError` with message: \"router_url and workload_manager_url are required in agent_metadata.yaml for AgentCube provider\"\n\n**Deployment flow:**\n1. Initialize `AgentCubeProvider` with namespace from options/metadata/default\n2. Call `provider.deploy_agent_runtime()` with:\n   - `agent_name`: from metadata\n   - `image_url`: prepared image URL\n   - `port`: from metadata\n   - `entrypoint`: from metadata (optional)\n   - `env_vars`: merged from metadata and options\n   - `workload_manager_url`: from metadata\n   - `router_url`: from metadata\n   - `readiness_probe_path`: from metadata (optional)\n   - `readiness_probe_port`: from metadata (optional)\n3. Wait for CR readiness (poll CR status)\n4. Extract agent endpoint from CR status\n5. Return deployment result with `agent_id`, `endpoint`, `namespace`\n\n**CR details:**\n- API Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n- Version: `v1alpha1`\n- Plural: `agentruntimes`\n- Session config: `sessionTimeout: \"15m\"`, `maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"`\n- Image pull secrets: `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n\n### Kubernetes Provider: `_publish_k8s()`\n\n```python\ndef _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n```\n\n**Deployment flow:**\n1. Initialize `KubernetesProvider` with namespace from options/metadata/default\n2. Call `provider.deploy_agent()` with:\n   - `agent_name`: from metadata (sanitized)\n   - `image_url`: prepared image URL\n   - `port`: from metadata\n   - `entrypoint`: from metadata (optional)\n   - `replicas`: from options (default: 1)\n   - `node_port`: from options (optional, range 30000-32767)\n   - `env_vars`: merged from metadata and options\n3. Wait for deployment readiness via `provider.wait_for_deployment_ready(timeout=120)`\n4. On timeout, raise `RuntimeError` after recording error in metadata\n5. Extract service URL from deployment result\n6. Return deployment result with `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `service_url`, `namespace`\n\n**Service URL format:** `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n\n### Metadata Updates\n\n#### `_update_publish_metadata()`\n\n```python\ndef _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n```\n\n**Updates to metadata:**\n- `agent_id`: from deployment result\n- `agent_endpoint`: service URL or CR endpoint\n- `k8s_deployment`: deployment metadata dict including:\n  - `type`: `\"AgentRuntime\"` or `\"Deployment\"`\n  - `namespace`\n  - `deployment_name` / `cr_name`\n  - `service_url`\n- `version`: if specified in options\n- `description`: if specified in options\n- `region`: if specified in options\n\nSaves updated metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml`.\n\n---\n\n## Provider Implementations\n\n### AgentCubeProvider\n\n**File:** `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n\n**Key method:** `deploy_agent_runtime()`\n\n**CR spec structure:**\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: AgentRuntime\nmetadata:\n  name: <sanitized-agent-name>\n  namespace: <namespace>\nspec:\n  image: <image-url>\n  port: <port>\n  entrypoint: <entrypoint>  # optional\n  env:\n    - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n      value: <workload-manager-url>\n    - name: ROUTER_URL\n      value: <router-url>\n  sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n  maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n  imagePullSecrets:\n    - name: default-secret\n  readinessProbe:  # if probe fields provided\n    path: <readiness_probe_path>\n    port: <readiness_probe_port>\n```\n\n**Environment variable fallback:**\n- If `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` not in env_vars, use `os.environ.get(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")`\n- If `ROUTER_URL` not in env_vars, use `os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")`\n\n**Name sanitization:** `_sanitize_name()` converts to lowercase, replaces invalid chars with `-`, truncates to 63 chars.\n\n### KubernetesProvider\n\n**File:** `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n\n**Key method:** `deploy_agent()`\n\n**Creates:**\n1. Deployment with container spec (image, port, entrypoint, env vars, replicas)\n2. NodePort Service exposing the deployment\n\n**Deployment spec:**\n```yaml\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: <sanitized-name>\n  namespace: <namespace>\nspec:\n  replicas: <replicas>\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: <sanitized-name>\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: <sanitized-name>\n    spec:\n      containers:\n        - name: <sanitized-name>\n          image: <image-url>\n          ports:\n            - containerPort: <port>\n          env: <env_vars>\n```\n\n**Service spec:**\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: <sanitized-name>\n  namespace: <namespace>\nspec:\n  type: NodePort\n  selector:\n    app: <sanitized-name>\n  ports:\n    - port: <port>\n      targetPort: <port>\n      nodePort: <node-port>  # optional, auto-assigned if not provided\n```\n\n**Readiness wait:**\n- Polls deployment status every 2 seconds\n- Timeout: 120 seconds (configurable)\n- Raises `TimeoutError` if not ready within timeout\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Prerequisite Errors\n\n| Condition | Exception | Message |\n|-----------|-----------|---------|\n| Workspace not found | `ValueError` | \"Workspace directory does not exist: {path}\" |\n| Docker unavailable (local mode) | `RuntimeError` | \"Docker is not available or not running\" |\n| Missing image URL (local mode) | `ValueError` | \"Image URL is required for local build mode\" |\n| Missing router_url (agentcube provider) | `ValueError` | \"router_url and workload_manager_url are required in agent_metadata.yaml for AgentCube provider\" |\n| Invalid node_port range | `ValueError` | \"NodePort must be between 30000 and 32767\" |\n| Deployment readiness timeout | `RuntimeError` | \"Deployment {name} did not become ready within {timeout}s\" |\n\n### CLI Error Handling\n\nVia `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)`:\n- Print `Error publish: {e}` in red\n- If `verbose=True`, print full traceback\n- Exit with code 1\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Internal\n\n- `MetadataService`: Load/save/validate workspace metadata\n- `DockerService`: Build/push images (local mode)\n- `AgentCubeProvider`: Deploy AgentRuntime CR\n- `KubernetesProvider`: Deploy standard K8s resources\n\n### External (Python packages)\n\n- `typer`: CLI framework\n- `pydantic`: Metadata validation\n- `pyyaml`: Metadata file I/O\n- `docker`: Docker SDK for Python (local builds)\n- `kubernetes`: K8s client library (optional, for K8s provider)\n- `rich`: Progress spinner and output formatting\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Test Case | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `test_publish_local_mode` | Local build mode with Docker image push |\n| `test_publish_cloud_mode` | Cloud build mode with image URL resolution |\n| `test_publish_agentcube_provider` | AgentRuntime CR deployment |\n| `test_publish_k8s_provider` | Standard K8s Deployment/Service |\n| `test_publish_missing_router_url` | Validation error for missing router_url |\n| `test_publish_missing_workload_manager_url` | Validation error for missing workload_manager_url |\n| `test_publish_invalid_node_port` | Validation error for out-of-range node_port |\n| `test_publish_docker_unavailable` | RuntimeError when Docker not available |\n| `test_publish_metadata_update` | Metadata file updated with deployment info |\n| `test_publish_version_override` | Version from CLI options applied |\n| `test_publish_readiness_timeout` | TimeoutError when deployment not ready |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Test Case | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `test_publish_e2e_local_agentcube` | Full flow: local build → push → CR deploy |\n| `test_publish_e2e_local_k8s` | Full flow: local build → push → K8s deploy |\n| `test_publish_e2e_cloud_agentcube` | Full flow: cloud image → CR deploy |\n\n---\n\n## Output Format\n\n### Success Output\n\n```\n✓ Agent published successfully\n  Agent: <agent_name>\n  Provider: <agentcube|k8s>\n  Namespace: <namespace>\n  Endpoint: <endpoint_url>\n  Version: <version>\n```\n\n### AgentCube Provider Additional Output\n\n```\n  Agent ID: <agent_id>\n  Session Timeout: 15m\n  Max Session Duration: 8h\n```\n\n### K8s Provider Additional Output\n\n```\n  Deployment: <deployment_name>\n  Service: <service_name>\n  NodePort: <node_port>\n  Replicas: <replicas>\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Image preparation is provider-agnostic** — the same image URL is used regardless of target provider\n2. **Metadata is the source of truth** — CLI options override metadata, but metadata is updated with final deployment state\n3. **Namespace resolution order:** CLI option → metadata → default (\"default\")\n4. **Version handling:** If `--version` provided, update metadata; otherwise use existing metadata version or \"latest\"\n5. **Credential security:** Image credentials passed via CLI options are not logged even in verbose mode\n6. **Concurrent deployments:** No locking mechanism; concurrent publishes to same namespace may cause conflicts\n7. **CR status polling:** AgentCube provider polls CR status field for readiness; no equivalent wait for K8s provider beyond deployment readiness\n\n---\n\n## Migration Notes\n\n- Existing `agentcube.yaml` references should be treated as naming drift; canonical file is `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- Loading falls back to `agent.yaml` then `metadata.yaml` for backwards compatibility\n- No automatic migration of old metadata files; manual update recommended\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775854034762,"end":1775854034768}}}}
