{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775854053888,"sessionID":"ses_286db11edffe7MbduyFHkzy6Ym","part":{"id":"prt_d79266784001ws93AsGlX4h6j1","messageID":"msg_d79262eb300190gIuQT5PoD4TO","sessionID":"ses_286db11edffe7MbduyFHkzy6Ym","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_95fb59d51ac44bfb817b4621","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-022/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-022/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 — Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: <!-- TODO: 设计概述 -->\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: <!-- TODO: 架构设计 -->\n10: \n11: ## Component Design\n12: \n13: <!-- TODO: 组件设计细节 -->\n14: \n15: ## Data Flow\n16: \n17: <!-- TODO: 数据流描述 -->\n18: \n19: ## Error Handling\n20: \n21: <!-- TODO: 错误处理策略 -->\n22: \n23: ## Testing Strategy\n24: \n25: <!-- TODO: 测试策略 -->\n\n(End of file - total 25 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 — Design\n\n## Overview\n\n<!-- TODO: 设计概述 -->\n\n## Architecture\n\n<!-- TODO: 架构设计 -->\n\n## Component Design\n\n<!-- TODO: 组件设计细节 -->\n\n## Data Flow\n\n<!-- TODO: 数据流描述 -->\n\n## Error Handling\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","time":{"start":1775854053878,"end":1775854053887}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775854054789,"sessionID":"ses_286db11edffe7MbduyFHkzy6Ym","part":{"id":"prt_d79266a6d001heNwY55Aop9kCD","messageID":"msg_d79262eb300190gIuQT5PoD4TO","sessionID":"ses_286db11edffe7MbduyFHkzy6Ym","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_50c7e109ab6a40fe9c9b7b7c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-020: CLI pack 命令 — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: The `pack` command validates and prepares an agent workspace for the AgentCube lifecycle. It performs workspace structure validation, merges CLI overrides into agent metadata, optionally generates a language-specific `Dockerfile`, infers missing configuration (entrypoint, agent name), and persists the final `agent_metadata.yaml`. It is the first step in the agent pipeline: `pack → build → publish → invoke`.\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 Data Flow\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                      CLI (Typer)                              │\n14: │   kubectl-agentcube pack -f <workspace> [--agent-name ...]    │\n15: └────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘\n16:                          │ options dict\n17:                          ▼\n18: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n19: │                    PackRuntime                                │\n20: │  ┌─────────────┬──────────────┬──────────────┬────────────┐  │\n21: │  │ _validate_  │ _load_or_    │ _apply_      │ _validate_ │  │\n22: │  │ workspace   │ create_meta  │ option_      │ language_  │  │\n23: │  │ _structure  │              │ overrides    │ compat     │  │\n24: │  └──────┬──────┴──────┬───────┴──────┬───────┴─────┬──────┘  │\n25: │         │             │              │             │          │\n26: │         ▼             ▼              ▼             ▼          │\n27: │  filesystem check  YAML load    metadata merge   .py/.pom    │\n28: │                     /create      + defaults      validation  │\n29: │                                                              │\n30: │  ┌─────────────┬──────────────┬──────────────┬────────────┐  │\n31: │  │ _process_   │ _generate_   │ _update_     │ _prepare_  │  │\n32: │  │ dependencies│ dockerfile   │ pack_meta    │ output_    │  │\n33: │  │             │              │              │ path       │  │\n34: │  └──────┬──────┴──────┬───────┴──────┬───────┴─────┬──────┘  │\n35: │         │             │              │             │          │\n36: │         ▼             ▼              ▼             ▼          │\n37: │  pip/maven       Dockerfile     metadata.yaml   output dir   │\n38: │  scan            template       saved         resolution    │\n39: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n40:                          │\n41:                          ▼\n42: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n43: │                  Rich Progress Spinner                        │\n44: │  \"✓ Agent 'my-agent' packaged successfully!\"                  │\n45: │  Workspace: /path/to/workspace                                │\n46: │  Metadata:  /path/to/workspace/agent_metadata.yaml            │\n47: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n48: ```\n49: \n50: ### 1.3 Package Layout (pack-relevant modules)\n51: \n52: ```\n53: cmd/cli/\n54: ├── pyproject.toml                     — Dependencies, console script entry\n55: ├── agentcube/\n56: │   ├── __init__.py                    — __version__, PackRuntime export\n57: │   ├── cli/\n58: │   │   ├── __init__.py                — Subpackage marker\n59: │   │   └── main.py                    — Typer app, pack() command, _handle_error\n60: │   ├── models/\n61: │   │   └── pack_models.py             — MetadataOptions dataclass\n62: │   ├── runtime/\n63: │   │   ├── __init__.py                — Re-exports PackRuntime, MetadataOptions\n64: │   │   └── pack_runtime.py            — PackRuntime class\n65: │   └── services/\n66: │       ├── __init__.py                — Services package docstring\n67: │       ├── metadata_service.py         — AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n68: │       └── docker_service.py           — DockerService (used by build, not pack)\n69: └── examples/\n70:     ├── hello-agent/main.py            — Example Python agent\n71:     └── math-agent/main.py             — Example Python agent\n72: ```\n73: \n74: ### 1.4 Dependencies\n75: \n76: | Module | Purpose |\n77: |--------|---------|\n78: | `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework, Rich markup |\n79: | `pydantic>=2.0.0` | AgentMetadata validation |\n80: | `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML load/dump for agent_metadata.yaml |\n81: | `rich>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner, colored output |\n82: | `packaging>=23.0` | Language/runtime version detection |\n83: | `importlib-resources>=6.0.0` | Dockerfile template access |\n84: | `semver>=3.0.0` | Version handling (indirect, used by build) |\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## 2. Data Structures\n89: \n90: ### 2.1 PackRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n91: \n92: ```python\n93: class PackRuntime:\n94:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n95:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n96:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n97:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n98:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n99:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n100:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n101:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n102:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n103:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n104:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n105:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n106:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n107:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n108:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None: ...\n109:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path: ...\n110:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str: ...\n111: ```\n112: \n113: ### 2.2 MetadataOptions (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n114: \n115: ```python\n116: @dataclass\n117: class MetadataOptions:\n118:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n119:     language: Optional[str] = 'python'\n120:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n121:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n122:     build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'\n123:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n124:     description: Optional[str] = None\n125:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n126:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n127:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n128:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n129:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n130:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n131:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n132:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n133: \n134:     @classmethod\n135:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\": ...\n136: ```\n137: \n138: ### 2.3 AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n139: \n140: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n141: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n142: | `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n143: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n144: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n145: | `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n146: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n147: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n148: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n149: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string for publishing |\n150: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image information |\n151: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication configuration |\n152: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n153: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for image publishing |\n154: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n155: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n156: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n157: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Workload Manager |\n158: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Router |\n159: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path for the readiness probe |\n160: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port for the readiness probe |\n161: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n162: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The session ID for the agent |\n163: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment information |\n164: \n165: **Validators:**\n166: - `validate_language` → must be `python` or `java` (lowercased)\n167: - `validate_build_mode` → must be `local` or `cloud` (lowercased)\n168: - `validate_port` → must be in range `1..65535`\n169: \n170: ### 2.4 Sentinel Errors\n171: \n172: ```python\n173: # PackRuntime\n174: ValueError(\"Workspace directory does not exist: {path}\")\n175: ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n176: ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in Java workspace\")\n177: ValueError(\"Unsupported language: {language}\")\n178: ValueError(\"Entrypoint is required but could not be inferred\")\n179: RuntimeError(\"Failed to generate Dockerfile: {reason}\")\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## 3. API Contracts\n185: \n186: ### 3.1 CLI Command Signature\n187: \n188: ```\n189: kubectl-agentcube pack [OPTIONS]\n190: ```\n191: \n192: | Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n193: |--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n194: | `--workspace` | `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n195: | `--agent-name` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override the agent name |\n196: | `--language` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Programming language (python, java) |\n197: | `--entrypoint` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override the entrypoint command |\n198: | `--port` | — | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port to expose in the Dockerfile |\n199: | `--build-mode` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n200: | `--description` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n201: | `--output` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Output path for packaged workspace |\n202: | `--verbose` | — | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n203: \n204: ### 3.2 Successful Pack Output\n205: \n206: ```\n207: ✓ Agent 'my-agent' packaged successfully!\n208:   Workspace: /path/to/workspace\n209:   Metadata:  /path/to/workspace/agent_metadata.yaml\n210: ```\n211: \n212: ### 3.3 Error Output (verbose=True)\n213: \n214: ```\n215: Error packaging agent: <error message>\n216: <full traceback>\n217: ```\n218: \n219: Exit code: `1`\n220: \n221: ### 3.4 Error Output (verbose=False)\n222: \n223: ```\n224: Error packaging agent: <error message>\n225: ```\n226: \n227: Exit code: `1`\n228: \n229: ### 3.5 Metadata File Format\n230: \n231: **Primary filename:** `agent_metadata.yaml`  \n232: **Load fallbacks:** `agent.yaml` → `metadata.yaml`\n233: \n234: **Save format:**\n235: ```yaml\n236: agent_name: my-agent\n237: language: python\n238: entrypoint: python main.py\n239: port: 8080\n240: build_mode: local\n241: # ... other fields, None values excluded\n242: ```\n243: \n244: Written with `yaml.dump(default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)` after `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`.\n245: \n246: ### 3.6 Workspace Validation Rules\n247: \n248: | Language | Requirement | Error if Missing |\n249: |----------|-------------|------------------|\n250: | Any | Directory exists | `ValueError(\"Workspace directory does not exist: {path}\")` |\n251: | Python | At least one `*.py` file in workspace root | `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")` |\n252: | Java | `pom.xml` in workspace root | `ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in Java workspace\")` |\n253: \n254: ### 3.7 Dockerfile Generation\n255: \n256: **When generated:** If no `Dockerfile` exists in the workspace root.\n257: \n258: **Python Dockerfile template:**\n259: ```dockerfile\n260: FROM python:3.10-slim\n261: WORKDIR /app\n262: COPY requirements.txt .\n263: RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n264: COPY . .\n265: EXPOSE {port}\n266: CMD {entrypoint}\n267: ```\n268: \n269: **Java Dockerfile template:**\n270: ```dockerfile\n271: FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS build\n272: WORKDIR /app\n273: COPY pom.xml .\n274: RUN mvn dependency:go-offline\n275: COPY src ./src\n276: RUN mvn package -DskipTests\n277: \n278: FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre-alpine\n279: WORKDIR /app\n280: COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar\n281: EXPOSE {port}\n282: CMD {entrypoint}\n283: ```\n284: \n285: ### 3.8 Entrypoint Inference\n286: \n287: | Language | Inference Logic |\n288: |----------|-----------------|\n289: | Python | Find first `*.py` file in workspace root; default to `python <file>` |\n290: | Java | Default to `java -jar app.jar` |\n291: \n292: If inference fails and no `--entrypoint` provided: raise `ValueError(\"Entrypoint is required but could not be inferred\")`.\n293: \n294: ### 3.9 Dependency Processing\n295: \n296: | Language | Detection | Action |\n297: |----------|-----------|--------|\n298: | Python | `requirements.txt` exists | Validate file is readable; set `requirements_file` in metadata |\n299: | Python | `requirements.txt` missing | Create empty file in workspace |\n300: | Java | `pom.xml` exists | Validate XML is parseable |\n301: | Java | `pom.xml` missing | Already caught by workspace validation |\n302: \n303: ---\n304: \n305: ## 4. Core Implementation\n306: \n307: ### 4.1 pack() Entry Point (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n308: \n309: ```python\n310: @app.command()\n311: def pack(\n312:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"...\", show_default=True),\n313:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"...\"),\n314:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"...\"),\n315:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"...\"),\n316:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"...\"),\n317:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"...\"),\n318:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"...\"),\n319:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"...\"),\n320:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"...\"),\n321: ) -> None:\n322:     with Progress(SpinnerColumn(), TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"), transient=True) as progress:\n323:         task = progress.add_task(\"Packaging agent...\", total=None)\n324:         try:\n325:             runtime = PackRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n326:             workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n327:             result = runtime.pack(workspace_path,\n328:                 agent_name=agent_name, language=language, entrypoint=entrypoint,\n329:                 port=port, build_mode=build_mode, description=description, output=output,\n330:             )\n331:             progress.update(task, description=\"Done\")\n332:             console.print(f\"[green]✓[/green] Agent '[bold]{result['agent_name']}[/bold]' packaged successfully!\")\n333:             console.print(f\"  [dim]Workspace:[/dim] {result['workspace_path']}\")\n334:             console.print(f\"  [dim]Metadata: [/dim] {result['metadata_path']}\")\n335:         except Exception as e:\n336:             _handle_error(e, \"packaging agent\", verbose)\n337: ```\n338: \n339: ### 4.2 PackRuntime.pack() — Main Orchestration\n340: \n341: ```python\n342: def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n343:     # 1. Validate workspace structure\n344:     self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n345: \n346:     # 2. Build options dict from CLI args\n347:     opts = MetadataOptions.from_options(options)\n348:     options_dict = asdict(opts)\n349: \n350:     # 3. Load existing metadata or create new\n351:     metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options_dict)\n352: \n353:     # 4. Apply CLI overrides\n354:     metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options_dict)\n355: \n356:     # 5. Validate language compatibility\n357:     self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n358: \n359:     # 6. Process dependencies\n360:     self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n361: \n362:     # 7. Generate Dockerfile if missing\n363:     dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n364: \n365:     # 8. Update and save metadata\n366:     self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n367: \n368:     # 9. Prepare output path\n369:     final_workspace = self._prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get(\"output\"))\n370: \n371:     return {\n372:         \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n373:         \"workspace_path\": str(final_workspace),\n374:         \"metadata_path\": str(final_workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"),\n375:     }\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ### 4.3 _validate_workspace_structure\n379: \n380: ```python\n381: def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n382:     if not workspace_path.exists():\n383:         raise ValueError(f\"Workspace directory does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n384:     if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n385:         raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n386: ```\n387: \n388: Language-specific checks deferred to `_validate_language_compatibility`.\n389: \n390: ### 4.4 _load_or_create_metadata\n391: \n392: ```python\n393: def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n394:     service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n395: \n396:     # Try primary file, then fallbacks\n397:     primary = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n398:     fallbacks = [workspace_path / \"agent.yaml\", workspace_path / \"metadata.yaml\"]\n399: \n400:     if primary.exists():\n401:         return service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n402: \n403:     for fb in fallbacks:\n404:         if fb.exists():\n405:             return service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n406: \n407:     # Create new metadata from options\n408:     agent_name = options.get(\"agent_name\") or workspace_path.name\n409:     return AgentMetadata(\n410:         agent_name=agent_name,\n411:         language=options.get(\"language\", \"python\") or \"python\",\n412:         entrypoint=options.get(\"entrypoint\", \"\"),\n413:         port=options.get(\"port\", 8080) or 8080,\n414:         build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\", \"local\") or \"local\",\n415:         description=options.get(\"description\"),\n416:     )\n417: ```\n418: \n419: ### 4.5 _apply_option_overrides\n420: \n421: ```python\n422: def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n423:     updates = {}\n424:     for key in [\"agent_name\", \"language\", \"entrypoint\", \"port\", \"build_mode\",\n425:                 \"description\", \"region\", \"workload_manager_url\", \"router_url\",\n426:                 \"readiness_probe_path\", \"readiness_probe_port\",\n427:                 \"registry_url\", \"registry_username\", \"registry_password\", \"agent_endpoint\"]:\n428:         value = options.get(key)\n429:         if value is not None and value != \"\":\n430:             updates[key] = value\n431: \n432:     if updates:\n433:         service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n434:         metadata = service.update_metadata(Path(\".\"), updates)  # workspace resolved internally\n435: \n436:     # Infer entrypoint if still missing\n437:     if not metadata.entrypoint:\n438:         metadata.entrypoint = self._infer_entrypoint(\n439:             Path(\".\"), metadata.language  # workspace resolved internally\n440:         )\n441: \n442:     return metadata\n443: ```\n444: \n445: ### 4.6 _validate_language_compatibility\n446: \n447: ```python\n448: def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n449:     if metadata.language == \"python\":\n450:         self._validate_python_compatibility(workspace_path)\n451:     elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n452:         self._validate_java_compatibility(workspace_path)\n453:     else:\n454:         raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {metadata.language}\")\n455: ```\n456: \n457: ### 4.7 _validate_python_compatibility\n458: \n459: ```python\n460: def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n461:     py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n462:     if not py_files:\n463:         raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n464: ```\n465: \n466: ### 4.8 _validate_java_compatibility\n467: \n468: ```python\n469: def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n470:     pom = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n471:     if not pom.exists():\n472:         raise ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in Java workspace\")\n473: ```\n474: \n475: ### 4.9 _process_dependencies\n476: \n477: ```python\n478: def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n479:     if metadata.language == \"python\":\n480:         self._process_python_dependencies(workspace_path)\n481:     elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n482:         self._process_java_dependencies(workspace_path)\n483: ```\n484: \n485: ### 4.10 _process_python_dependencies\n486: \n487: ```python\n488: def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n489:     req_file = workspace_path / \"requirements.txt\"\n490:     if not req_file.exists():\n491:         req_file.touch()\n492: ```\n493: \n494: ### 4.11 _process_java_dependencies\n495: \n496: ```python\n497: def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n498:     # pom.xml already validated; no additional processing needed\n499:     pass\n500: ```\n501: \n502: ### 4.12 _generate_dockerfile\n503: \n504: ```python\n505: def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]:\n506:     dockerfile = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n507:     if dockerfile.exists():\n508:         return dockerfile\n509: \n510:     if metadata.language == \"python\":\n511:         content = self._generate_python_dockerfile(metadata)\n512:     elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n513:         content = self._generate_java_dockerfile(metadata)\n514:     else:\n515:         return None\n516: \n517:     dockerfile.write_text(content)\n518:     return dockerfile\n519: ```\n520: \n521: ### 4.13 _generate_python_dockerfile\n522: \n523: ```python\n524: def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n525:     return f\"\"\"FROM python:3.10-slim\n526: WORKDIR /app\n527: COPY requirements.txt .\n528: RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n529: COPY . .\n530: EXPOSE {metadata.port}\n531: CMD {metadata.entrypoint}\n532: \"\"\"\n533: ```\n534: \n535: ### 4.14 _generate_java_dockerfile\n536: \n537: ```python\n538: def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n539:     return f\"\"\"FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS build\n540: WORKDIR /app\n541: COPY pom.xml .\n542: RUN mvn dependency:go-offline\n543: COPY src ./src\n544: RUN mvn package -DskipTests\n545: \n546: FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre-alpine\n547: WORKDIR /app\n548: COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar\n549: EXPOSE {metadata.port}\n550: CMD {metadata.entrypoint}\n551: \"\"\"\n552: ```\n553: \n554: ### 4.15 _update_pack_metadata\n555: \n556: ```python\n557: def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None:\n558:     service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n559:     service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n560: ```\n561: \n562: ### 4.16 _prepare_output_path\n563: \n564: ```python\n565: def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path:\n566:     if output_path:\n567:         out = Path(output_path).resolve()\n568:         out.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n569:         return out\n570:     return workspace_path\n571: ```\n572: \n573: ### 4.17 _infer_entrypoint\n574: \n575: ```python\n576: def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n577:     if language == \"python\":\n578:         py_files = sorted(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n579:         if py_files:\n580:             return f\"python {py_files[0].name}\"\n581:         raise ValueError(\"Entrypoint is required but could not be inferred\")\n582:     elif language == \"java\":\n583:         return \"java -jar app.jar\"\n584:     raise ValueError(f\"Cannot infer entrypoint for language: {language}\")\n585: ```\n586: \n587: ### 4.18 _handle_error (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n588: \n589: ```python\n590: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n591:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n592:     if verbose:\n593:         console.print_exception()\n594:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n595: ```\n596: \n597: ---\n598: \n599: ## 5. Configuration\n600: \n601: ### 5.1 CLI Options → Metadata Mapping\n602: \n603: | CLI Option | Metadata Field | Override Behavior |\n604: |------------|----------------|-------------------|\n605: | `--agent-name` | `agent_name` | Direct override |\n606: | `--language` | `language` | Direct override, validated against `['python', 'java']` |\n607: | `--entrypoint` | `entrypoint` | Direct override; if omitted, inferred from workspace |\n608: | `--port` | `port` | Direct override; default `8080` |\n609: | `--build-mode` | `build_mode` | Direct override, validated against `['local', 'cloud']` |\n610: | `--description` | `description` | Direct override |\n611: | `--output` | — | Controls output directory, not persisted to metadata |\n612: | `--verbose` | — | Controls logging level and error detail |\n613: \n614: ### 5.2 Metadata Defaults Cascade\n615: \n616: 1. **Existing `agent_metadata.yaml`** → loaded values\n617: 2. **Fallback files** (`agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`) → loaded values\n618: 3. **CLI options** → override loaded values (if non-None, non-empty)\n619: 4. **Hardcoded defaults** → fill remaining gaps (`language=python`, `port=8080`, `build_mode=local`)\n620: 5. **Inference** → `entrypoint` derived from workspace files, `agent_name` from directory name\n621: \n622: ---\n623: \n624: ## 6. Testing Strategy\n625: \n626: ### 6.1 Unit Test Matrix\n627: \n628: #### PackRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_pack_runtime.py`)\n629: \n630: | Test Name | Description |\n631: |-----------|-------------|\n632: | `TestPackRuntime_ValidPythonWorkspace` | Valid Python workspace with `main.py` → packs successfully |\n633: | `TestPackRuntime_ValidJavaWorkspace` | Valid Java workspace with `pom.xml` → packs successfully |\n634: | `TestPackRuntime_MissingWorkspace` | Non-existent path → `ValueError` |\n635: | `TestPackRuntime_NoPythonFiles` | Python language, no `*.py` → `ValueError(\"No Python files found\")` |\n636: | `TestPackRuntime_NoPomXml` | Java language, no `pom.xml` → `ValueError(\"pom.xml not found\")` |\n637: | `TestPackRuntime_UnsupportedLanguage` | `language=ruby` → `ValueError(\"Unsupported language\")` |\n638: | `TestPackRuntime_ExistingMetadata` | `agent_metadata.yaml` present → loads and merges |\n639: | `TestPackRuntime_FallbackMetadata` | Only `agent.yaml` present → loads from fallback |\n640: | `TestPackRuntime_NoMetadata` | No metadata files → creates new from options |\n641: | `TestPackRuntime_CliOverrides` | CLI `--agent-name` overrides existing metadata |\n642: | `TestPackRuntime_InferEntrypointPython` | No entrypoint, Python workspace → infers `python main.py` |\n643: | `TestPackRuntime_InferEntrypointJava` | No entrypoint, Java workspace → infers `java -jar app.jar` |\n644: | `TestPackRuntime_InferEntrypointFails` | No `*.py` files, no entrypoint → `ValueError` |\n645: | `TestPackRuntime_GeneratePythonDockerfile` | No Dockerfile, Python → generates correct Dockerfile |\n646: | `TestPackRuntime_GenerateJavaDockerfile` | No Dockerfile, Java → generates correct Dockerfile |\n647: | `TestPackRuntime_ExistingDockerfile` | Dockerfile exists → not regenerated |\n648: | `TestPackRuntime_CreateRequirementsTxt` | Python workspace without `requirements.txt` → creates empty file |\n649: | `TestPackRuntime_OutputPath` | `--output` specified → returns output path, not workspace |\n650: | `TestPackRuntime_MetadataSavedCorrectly` | Metadata file written with correct YAML format |\n651: | `TestPackRuntime_PortValidation` | `--port=0` → Pydantic validation error |\n652: | `TestPackRuntime_PortValidationHigh` | `--port=70000` → Pydantic validation error |\n653: \n654: #### CLI Command Tests (`tests/cli/test_pack_command.py`)\n655: \n656: | Test Name | Description |\n657: |-----------|-------------|\n658: | `TestPackCommand_Success` | `pack -f <valid_workspace>` → success output, exit 0 |\n659: | `TestPackCommand_Defaults` | `pack` (no options) → uses `workspace=\".\"` |\n660: | `TestPackCommand_VerboseError` | Exception + `--verbose` → red error + traceback, exit 1 |\n661: | `TestPackCommand_QuietError` | Exception, no `--verbose` → red error only, exit 1 |\n662: | `TestPackCommand_ProgressSpinner` | Runs with Rich Progress spinner visible |\n663: \n664: #### MetadataService Tests (`tests/services/test_metadata_service.py`)\n665: \n666: | Test Name | Description |\n667: |-----------|-------------|\n668: | `TestMetadataService_SaveAndLoad` | Save → load round-trip preserves fields |\n669: | `TestMetadataService_FallbackLoad` | `agent.yaml` present, `agent_metadata.yaml` absent → loads fallback |\n670: | `TestMetadataService_ExcludeNone` | `None` fields excluded from YAML output |\n671: | `TestMetadataService_YamlFormat` | Output uses `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, `default_flow_style=False` |\n672: \n673: #### MetadataOptions Tests (`tests/models/test_pack_models.py`)\n674: \n675: | Test Name | Description |\n676: |-----------|-------------|\n677: | `TestMetadataOptions_FromOptions` | `from_options({...})` → correct dataclass fields |\n678: | `TestMetadataOptions_Defaults` | Empty dict → default values applied |\n679: | `TestMetadataOptions_PartialOptions` | Partial dict → defaults fill gaps |\n680: \n681: ### 6.2 Test Helpers\n682: \n683: ```python\n684: @pytest.fixture\n685: def python_workspace(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n686:     ws = tmp_path / \"my-agent\"\n687:     ws.mkdir()\n688:     (ws / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\\n\")\n689:     return ws\n690: \n691: @pytest.fixture\n692: def java_workspace(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n693:     ws = tmp_path / \"java-agent\"\n694:     ws.mkdir()\n695:     (ws / \"pom.xml\").write_text(\"<project>...</project>\\n\")\n696:     (ws / \"src\").mkdir()\n697:     return ws\n698: \n699: @pytest.fixture\n700: def workspace_with_metadata(python_workspace: Path) -> Path:\n701:     metadata = python_workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n702:     metadata.write_text(\"agent_name: test-agent\\nlanguage: python\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nport: 8080\\nbuild_mode: local\\n\")\n703:     return python_workspace\n704: ```\n705: \n706: ### 6.3 Mock Strategy\n707: \n708: - **Filesystem:** Use `pytest` `tmp_path` fixture for isolated workspaces\n709: - **MetadataService:** Real instance (lightweight, no external deps)\n710: - **DockerService:** Not used by pack command; no mocking needed\n711: - **Console output:** Capture via `capfd` or `rich.console.Console(record=True)`\n712: \n713: ### 6.4 Gate Requirements\n714: \n715: 1. `pytest tests/ -v` all pass\n716: 2. `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` coverage ≥ 80%\n717: 3. `ruff check agentcube/` no violations\n718: 4. `mypy agentcube/` no type errors\n719: 5. All PackRuntime public methods have unit tests\n720: 6. Error paths tested (invalid workspace, missing files, bad language)\n721: \n722: ---\n723: \n724: ## 7. Deployment Considerations\n725: \n726: 1. **Workspace Path Resolution:** The `--workspace` path is resolved to absolute via `Path.resolve()` before any operations. Relative paths are supported but normalized.\n727: \n728: 2. **Metadata File Location:** Always written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`. If the workspace is read-only, pack will fail with a permission error.\n729: \n730: 3. **Dockerfile Generation:** Only generated if no `Dockerfile` exists. Custom Dockerfiles are preserved. The generated Dockerfile uses fixed base images (`python:3.10-slim`, `maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17`) — users needing different versions must provide their own.\n731: \n732: 4. **Requirements File:** For Python workspaces without `requirements.txt`, an empty file is created. This ensures the generated Dockerfile's `COPY requirements.txt` step succeeds.\n733: \n734: 5. **Output Path:** When `--output` is specified, the metadata is still saved to the original workspace, not the output directory. The output path is returned for downstream use (e.g., by a build system that copies the workspace).\n735: \n736: 6. **Language Validation:** Pydantic validators enforce `language ∈ {python, java}` and `build_mode ∈ {local, cloud}` at the metadata level. CLI-level validation is not performed; errors surface during metadata construction.\n737: \n738: ---\n739: \n740: ## 8. Implementation Steps\n741: \n742: ### Phase 1: Scaffolding (Day 1)\n743: \n744: 1. Create `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` with `PackRuntime` class skeleton\n745: 2. Create `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` with `MetadataOptions` dataclass\n746: 3. Implement `MetadataOptions.from_options()` classmethod\n747: 4. Write `MetadataOptions` tests\n748: \n749: ### Phase 2: Core Validation (Day 2)\n750: \n751: 1. Implement `_validate_workspace_structure`\n752: 2. Implement `_validate_python_compatibility` and `_validate_java_compatibility`\n753: 3. Implement `_validate_language_compatibility` dispatcher\n754: 4. Write validation tests (missing workspace, no Python files, no pom.xml)\n755: \n756: ### Phase 3: Metadata Handling (Day 3)\n757: \n758: 1. Implement `_load_or_create_metadata` with fallback logic\n759: 2. Implement `_apply_option_overrides`\n760: 3. Implement `_infer_entrypoint` for Python and Java\n761: 4. Write metadata tests (load, create, override, infer)\n762: \n763: ### Phase 4: Dockerfile & Dependencies (Day 4)\n764: \n765: 1. Implement `_process_dependencies`, `_process_python_dependencies`, `_process_java_dependencies`\n766: 2. Implement `_generate_dockerfile`, `_generate_python_dockerfile`, `_generate_java_dockerfile`\n767: 3. Implement `_update_pack_metadata`\n768: 4. Implement `_prepare_output_path`\n769: 5. Write Dockerfile generation tests\n770: \n771: ### Phase 5: CLI Integration & Polish (Day 5)\n772: \n773: 1. Implement `pack()` command in `agentcube/cli/main.py` with Rich Progress\n774: 2. Wire `_handle_error` for pack command\n775: 3. Implement `pack()` orchestration in `PackRuntime.pack()`\n776: 4. Run full test suite, fix gaps\n777: 5. Run `ruff check`, `mypy`, verify coverage\n778: \n779: ---\n780: \n781: ## 9. Future Changes\n782: \n783: | Change | Description | Priority |\n784: |--------|-------------|----------|\n785: | AR-0XX | Support for Node.js/Go workspaces | P2 |\n786: | AR-0XX | Custom Dockerfile templates from config | P2 |\n787: | AR-0XX | Multi-stage build optimization for Python (uv/pip-tools) | P3 |\n788: | AR-0XX | Workspace archive output (tar.gz) for cloud build mode | P2 |\n789: | AR-0XX | Pre-pack hook for custom validation scripts | P3 |\n790: \n791: ### Known Limitations\n792: \n793: - Only `python` and `java` languages are supported; other languages raise an error\n794: - Dockerfile templates use fixed base image versions; no customization via CLI\n795: - Entrypoint inference for Python picks the first `*.py` file alphabetically; may not be the correct main file\n796: - No validation that the inferred entrypoint actually runs successfully\n797: - Metadata is saved to the original workspace even when `--output` is specified; output directory receives no metadata file\n798: - No atomicity guarantee: if pack fails midway, partially generated files (Dockerfile, requirements.txt) may remain\n\n(End of file - total 798 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020: CLI pack 命令 — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThe `pack` command validates and prepares an agent workspace for the AgentCube lifecycle. It performs workspace structure validation, merges CLI overrides into agent metadata, optionally generates a language-specific `Dockerfile`, infers missing configuration (entrypoint, agent name), and persists the final `agent_metadata.yaml`. It is the first step in the agent pipeline: `pack → build → publish → invoke`.\n\n### 1.2 Data Flow\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      CLI (Typer)                              │\n│   kubectl-agentcube pack -f <workspace> [--agent-name ...]    │\n└────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘\n                         │ options dict\n                         ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    PackRuntime                                │\n│  ┌─────────────┬──────────────┬──────────────┬────────────┐  │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775854054775,"end":1775854054785}}}}
