{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775854164974,"sessionID":"ses_286db11edffe7MbduyFHkzy6Ym","part":{"id":"prt_d79268833001O6cnzr5yOcSj9Y","messageID":"msg_d79266dd3001X37gZdBru0N0St","sessionID":"ses_286db11edffe7MbduyFHkzy6Ym","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_5498d788bb6f48579de14339","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `publish` command deploys a packaged and built agent to a target Kubernetes cluster. It supports two providers:\n- **`agentcube`** (default): Deploys an AgentRuntime Custom Resource (CR) to `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n- **`k8s`**: Deploys standard Kubernetes Deployment + NodePort Service\n\nThe command handles image preparation (local Docker push or cloud image URL), provider-specific deployment, metadata updates, and readiness verification. It is the third step in the agent lifecycle pipeline: `pack → build → publish → invoke`.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### 2.1 Data Flow\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                          CLI (Typer)                                  │\n│   kubectl-agentcube publish -f <workspace> [--provider agentcube]    │\n└────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                         │ options dict\n                         ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                       PublishRuntime                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────┬──────────────────┬──────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │ _prepare_image_  │ _publish_cr_to_  │ _publish_k8s             │  │\n│  │ for_publishing   │ k8s              │                          │  │\n│  └────────┬─────────┴────────┬─────────┴────────────┬─────────────┘  │\n│           │                  │                      │                 │\n│           ▼                  ▼                      ▼                 │\n│  ┌────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────┐   │\n│  │ _prepare_local │  │ AgentCubeProvider│  │ KubernetesProvider │   │\n│  │ _image         │  │ .deploy_agent_   │  │ .deploy_agent()    │   │\n│  │ _prepare_cloud │  │ runtime()        │  │ .wait_for_deploy   │   │\n│  │ _image         │  │                  │  │ ment_ready()       │   │\n│  └────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └────────────────────┘   │\n│                                                                      │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │ _update_publish_metadata() → agent_metadata.yaml               │  │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                         │\n                         ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Rich Output                                        │\n│  \"✓ Agent published successfully\"                                    │\n│    Agent: <name>  Provider: <provider>  Endpoint: <url>              │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 2.2 Package Layout (publish-relevant modules)\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml                     — Dependencies, console script entry\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                    — __version__, PublishRuntime export\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                — Subpackage marker\n│   │   └── main.py                    — Typer app, publish() command, _handle_error\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   └── pack_models.py             — MetadataOptions dataclass\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                — Re-exports PublishRuntime\n│   │   └── publish_runtime.py         — PublishRuntime class\n│   └── services/\n│       ├── __init__.py                — Services package docstring\n│       ├── metadata_service.py         — AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n│       ├── docker_service.py           — DockerService (image push)\n│       ├── k8s_provider.py             — KubernetesProvider (Deployment + Service)\n│       └── agentcube_provider.py       — AgentCubeProvider (AgentRuntime CR)\n└── examples/\n    ├── hello-agent/main.py            — Example Python agent\n    └── math-agent/main.py             — Example Python agent\n```\n\n### 2.3 Dependencies\n\n| Module | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework, Rich markup |\n| `pydantic>=2.0.0` | AgentMetadata validation |\n| `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML load/dump for agent_metadata.yaml |\n| `docker>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for image push (local mode) |\n| `kubernetes>=28.0.0` | K8s client library (optional, for K8s provider) |\n| `rich>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner, colored output, tables |\n| `httpx>=0.24.0` | HTTP client (indirect, used by providers) |\n\n---\n\n## Component Design\n\n### 3.1 PublishRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`)\n\n```python\nclass PublishRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n    def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n    def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n    def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n    def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n```\n\n### 3.2 CLI Command Signature\n\n```\nkubectl-agentcube publish [OPTIONS]\n```\n\n| Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace` | `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n| `--version` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0) |\n| `--image-url` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Image repository URL (required in local build mode) |\n| `--image-username` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Username for image repository |\n| `--image-password` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Password for image repository |\n| `--description` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n| `--region` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n| `--cloud-provider` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n| `--provider` | — | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment/Service) |\n| `--node-port` | — | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Specific NodePort (30000-32767) for K8s deployment |\n| `--replicas` | — | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1) |\n| `--namespace` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The namespace for the deployment |\n| `--verbose` | — | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n\n### 3.3 Sentinel Errors\n\n```python\n# PublishRuntime\nValueError(\"Workspace directory does not exist: {path}\")\nValueError(\"Image URL is required for local build mode\")\nValueError(\"router_url and workload_manager_url are required in agent_metadata.yaml for AgentCube provider\")\nValueError(\"NodePort must be between 30000 and 32767\")\nRuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\nRuntimeError(\"Deployment {name} did not become ready within {timeout}s\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Flow\n\n### 4.1 publish() Main Orchestration\n\n```python\ndef publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    # 1. Validate workspace path\n    if not workspace_path.exists():\n        raise ValueError(f\"Workspace directory does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n    if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n        raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n\n    # 2. Load metadata\n    service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n    metadata = service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n\n    # 3. Apply CLI option overrides\n    for key in [\"version\", \"description\", \"region\"]:\n        value = options.get(key)\n        if value is not None:\n            setattr(metadata, key, value)\n\n    # 4. Validate node_port range if provided\n    node_port = options.get(\"node_port\")\n    if node_port is not None and not (30000 <= node_port <= 32767):\n        raise ValueError(\"NodePort must be between 30000 and 32767\")\n\n    # 5. Prepare image for publishing\n    image_url = self._prepare_image_for_publishing(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n\n    # 6. Route to provider-specific publish\n    if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n        result = self._publish_cr_to_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, image_url=image_url, **options)\n    elif self.provider == \"k8s\":\n        result = self._publish_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, image_url=image_url, **options)\n    else:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported provider: {self.provider}\")\n\n    # 7. Update metadata with deployment info\n    self._update_publish_metadata(workspace_path, result)\n\n    return result\n```\n\n### 4.2 Image Preparation Flow\n\n```\n_prepare_image_for_publishing()\n         │\n         ├── metadata.build_mode == \"local\"\n         │        │\n         │        ├── image_url from CLI required\n         │        │\n         │        └── _prepare_local_image()\n         │                 │\n         │                 ├── DockerService.check_docker_available()\n         │                 ├── DockerService._docker_login_sdk() (if credentials)\n         │                 └── DockerService.push_image()\n         │\n         └── metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\"\n                  │\n                  └── _prepare_cloud_image()\n                           │\n                           └── Resolve cloud image URL from metadata/options\n```\n\n### 4.3 _prepare_image_for_publishing\n\n```python\ndef _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n    if metadata.build_mode == \"local\":\n        return self._prepare_local_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n    elif metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\":\n        return self._prepare_cloud_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n    else:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build mode: {metadata.build_mode}\")\n```\n\n### 4.4 _prepare_local_image\n\n```python\ndef _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n    docker_service = DockerService(verbose=self.verbose)\n\n    if not docker_service.check_docker_available():\n        raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n\n    image_url = options.get(\"image_url\")\n    if not image_url:\n        raise ValueError(\"Image URL is required for local build mode\")\n\n    # Build image tag\n    version = metadata.version or \"latest\"\n    image_tag = f\"{image_url}:{version}\"\n\n    # Login if credentials provided\n    username = options.get(\"image_username\") or metadata.registry_username\n    password = options.get(\"image_password\") or metadata.registry_password\n    registry_url = options.get(\"registry_url\") or metadata.registry_url\n\n    if username and password:\n        docker_service._docker_login_sdk(registry_url, username, password)\n\n    # Push image\n    result = docker_service.push_image(image_tag, registry_url, username, password)\n    return result.get(\"pushed_image\", image_tag)\n```\n\n### 4.5 _prepare_cloud_image\n\n```python\ndef _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n    # Cloud build mode: image already built in cloud, resolve URL\n    image_url = options.get(\"image_url\")\n    if image_url:\n        return image_url\n\n    if metadata.image and metadata.image.get(\"url\"):\n        return metadata.image[\"url\"]\n\n    raise ValueError(\"Image URL is required for cloud build mode\")\n```\n\n### 4.6 AgentCube Provider Flow (_publish_cr_to_k8s)\n\n```python\ndef _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    # Validate prerequisites\n    if not metadata.router_url:\n        raise ValueError(\"router_url and workload_manager_url are required in agent_metadata.yaml for AgentCube provider\")\n    if not metadata.workload_manager_url:\n        raise ValueError(\"router_url and workload_manager_url are required in agent_metadata.yaml for AgentCube provider\")\n\n    # Initialize provider\n    namespace = options.get(\"namespace\") or \"default\"\n    provider = AgentCubeProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=self.verbose)\n\n    # Deploy AgentRuntime CR\n    result = provider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n        agent_name=metadata.agent_name,\n        image_url=options.get(\"image_url\", \"\"),\n        port=metadata.port,\n        entrypoint=metadata.entrypoint,\n        env_vars={},\n        workload_manager_url=metadata.workload_manager_url,\n        router_url=metadata.router_url,\n        readiness_probe_path=metadata.readiness_probe_path,\n        readiness_probe_port=metadata.readiness_probe_port,\n    )\n\n    # Wait for CR readiness (poll status)\n    # ... polling logic ...\n\n    return {\n        \"agent_id\": result.get(\"name\"),\n        \"agent_endpoint\": result.get(\"endpoint\"),\n        \"namespace\": namespace,\n        \"k8s_deployment\": {\n            \"type\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n            \"namespace\": namespace,\n            \"cr_name\": result.get(\"name\"),\n        },\n    }\n```\n\n### 4.7 Kubernetes Provider Flow (_publish_k8s)\n\n```python\ndef _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    namespace = options.get(\"namespace\") or \"default\"\n    replicas = options.get(\"replicas\") or 1\n    node_port = options.get(\"node_port\")\n\n    provider = KubernetesProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=self.verbose)\n\n    # Deploy Deployment + Service\n    result = provider.deploy_agent(\n        agent_name=metadata.agent_name,\n        image_url=options.get(\"image_url\", \"\"),\n        port=metadata.port,\n        entrypoint=metadata.entrypoint,\n        replicas=replicas,\n        node_port=node_port,\n        env_vars={},\n    )\n\n    # Wait for deployment readiness\n    try:\n        provider.wait_for_deployment_ready(result[\"deployment_name\"], timeout=120)\n    except TimeoutError:\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"Deployment {result['deployment_name']} did not become ready within 120s\")\n\n    return {\n        \"deployment_name\": result[\"deployment_name\"],\n        \"service_name\": result[\"service_name\"],\n        \"service_url\": result[\"service_url\"],\n        \"namespace\": namespace,\n        \"replicas\": replicas,\n        \"node_port\": result.get(\"node_port\"),\n        \"k8s_deployment\": {\n            \"type\": \"Deployment\",\n            \"namespace\": namespace,\n            \"deployment_name\": result[\"deployment_name\"],\n            \"service_url\": result[\"service_url\"],\n        },\n    }\n```\n\n### 4.8 _update_publish_metadata\n\n```python\ndef _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n    service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n    updates = {\n        \"agent_id\": agent_info.get(\"agent_id\"),\n        \"agent_endpoint\": agent_info.get(\"agent_endpoint\") or agent_info.get(\"service_url\"),\n        \"k8s_deployment\": agent_info.get(\"k8s_deployment\"),\n    }\n    service.update_metadata(workspace_path, updates)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### 5.1 Error Handling Strategy\n\n| Error Type | Handling | Exit Code |\n|------------|----------|-----------|\n| Workspace validation failure | `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` | 1 |\n| Docker unavailable (local mode) | `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` | 1 |\n| Missing image URL | `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` | 1 |\n| Missing router_url/workload_manager_url (agentcube) | `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` | 1 |\n| Invalid node_port range | `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` | 1 |\n| Deployment readiness timeout | `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` | 1 |\n| K8s client initialization failure | `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` | 1 |\n\n### 5.2 CLI Error Handler\n\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n    if verbose:\n        console.print_exception()\n    raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n### 5.3 Verbose vs Global Verbose\n\nThe subcommand's local `--verbose` flag is passed to `_handle_error`, ensuring traceback is printed even if global `-v` was not passed on the root callback.\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### 6.1 Unit Test Matrix\n\n#### PublishRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestPublishRuntime_ValidAgentCubePublish` | Valid workspace, agentcube provider → publishes CR successfully |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_ValidK8sPublish` | Valid workspace, k8s provider → publishes Deployment + Service |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_MissingWorkspace` | Non-existent path → `ValueError` |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_MissingImageUrlLocal` | Local build mode, no image_url → `ValueError` |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_MissingRouterUrl` | AgentCube provider, no router_url → `ValueError` |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_MissingWorkloadManagerUrl` | AgentCube provider, no workload_manager_url → `ValueError` |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_InvalidNodePort` | node_port=9999 → `ValueError` |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_DockerUnavailable` | Local mode, Docker down → `RuntimeError` |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_CloudImageResolution` | Cloud mode, image URL from metadata → resolves correctly |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_MetadataUpdate` | Metadata updated with deployment info after publish |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_VersionOverride` | `--version` overrides metadata version |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_DeploymentTimeout` | K8s deployment not ready → `RuntimeError` |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_UnsupportedProvider` | provider=\"unknown\" → `ValueError` |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_UnsupportedBuildMode` | build_mode=\"unknown\" → `ValueError` |\n\n#### CLI Command Tests (`tests/cli/test_publish_command.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestPublishCommand_SuccessAgentCube` | `publish --provider agentcube` → success output, exit 0 |\n| `TestPublishCommand_SuccessK8s` | `publish --provider k8s` → success output, exit 0 |\n| `TestPublishCommand_Defaults` | `publish` (no options) → uses defaults |\n| `TestPublishCommand_VerboseError` | Exception + `--verbose` → red error + traceback, exit 1 |\n| `TestPublishCommand_QuietError` | Exception, no `--verbose` → red error only, exit 1 |\n| `TestPublishCommand_ProgressSpinner` | Runs with Rich Progress spinner visible |\n\n#### AgentCubeProvider Tests (`tests/services/test_agentcube_provider.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestAgentCubeProvider_DeployCR` | Creates AgentRuntime CR with correct spec |\n| `TestAgentCubeProvider_EnvVarFallback` | Missing env vars fall back to os.environ |\n| `TestAgentCubeProvider_SessionConfig` | CR has sessionTimeout=15m, maxSessionDuration=8h |\n| `TestAgentCubeProvider_ImagePullSecrets` | CR has imagePullSecrets=[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}] |\n| `TestAgentCubeProvider_SanitizeName` | Invalid chars replaced, truncated to 63 chars |\n| `TestAgentCubeProvider_GetAgentRuntime` | Retrieves existing CR by name |\n\n#### KubernetesProvider Tests (`tests/services/test_k8s_provider.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestK8sProvider_DeployAgent` | Creates Deployment + NodePort Service |\n| `TestK8sProvider_WaitForReady` | Waits until deployment ready, returns |\n| `TestK8sProvider_WaitTimeout` | Timeout exceeded → `TimeoutError` |\n| `TestK8sProvider_NodePortRange` | NodePort in 30000-32767 range |\n| `TestK8sProvider_ServiceUrl` | Service URL format: `http://localhost:{node_port}` |\n| `TestK8sProvider_DeleteAgent` | Deletes Deployment + Service, ignores 404 |\n\n### 6.2 Test Helpers\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef workspace_with_metadata(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n    ws = tmp_path / \"my-agent\"\n    ws.mkdir()\n    (ws / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\\n\")\n    (ws / \"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n        \"agent_name: test-agent\\n\"\n        \"language: python\\n\"\n        \"entrypoint: python main.py\\n\"\n        \"port: 8080\\n\"\n        \"build_mode: local\\n\"\n        \"router_url: http://router.example.com\\n\"\n        \"workload_manager_url: http://wm.example.com\\n\"\n    )\n    return ws\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_docker_service(mocker):\n    service = mocker.patch(\"agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.DockerService\")\n    service.return_value.check_docker_available.return_value = True\n    service.return_value.push_image.return_value = {\"pushed_image\": \"registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0\"}\n    return service\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_agentcube_provider(mocker):\n    provider = mocker.patch(\"agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.AgentCubeProvider\")\n    provider.return_value.deploy_agent_runtime.return_value = {\n        \"name\": \"test-agent\",\n        \"endpoint\": \"http://router.example.com/v1/...\",\n    }\n    return provider\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_k8s_provider(mocker):\n    provider = mocker.patch(\"agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.KubernetesProvider\")\n    provider.return_value.deploy_agent.return_value = {\n        \"deployment_name\": \"test-agent\",\n        \"service_name\": \"test-agent\",\n        \"service_url\": \"http://localhost:30080\",\n        \"node_port\": 30080,\n    }\n    return provider\n```\n\n### 6.3 Mock Strategy\n\n- **Filesystem:** Use `pytest` `tmp_path` fixture for isolated workspaces\n- **MetadataService:** Real instance (lightweight, no external deps)\n- **DockerService:** Mock `check_docker_available`, `push_image`, `_docker_login_sdk`\n- **AgentCubeProvider:** Mock `deploy_agent_runtime`, `get_agent_runtime`\n- **KubernetesProvider:** Mock `deploy_agent`, `wait_for_deployment_ready`, `get_agent_status`\n- **Console output:** Capture via `capfd` or `rich.console.Console(record=True)`\n\n### 6.4 Gate Requirements\n\n1. `pytest tests/ -v` all pass\n2. `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` coverage ≥ 80%\n3. `ruff check agentcube/` no violations\n4. `mypy agentcube/` no type errors\n5. All PublishRuntime public methods have unit tests\n6. Error paths tested (invalid workspace, missing URLs, bad node_port, timeout)\n7. Both provider flows tested (agentcube and k8s)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Image preparation is provider-agnostic** — the same image URL is used regardless of target provider\n2. **Metadata is the source of truth** — CLI options override metadata, but metadata is updated with final deployment state\n3. **Namespace resolution order:** CLI option → metadata → default (\"default\")\n4. **Version handling:** If `--version` provided, update metadata; otherwise use existing metadata version or \"latest\"\n5. **Credential security:** Image credentials passed via CLI options are not logged even in verbose mode\n6. **Concurrent deployments:** No locking mechanism; concurrent publishes to same namespace may cause conflicts\n7. **CR status polling:** AgentCube provider polls CR status field for readiness; K8s provider uses `wait_for_deployment_ready` with 120s timeout\n8. **NodePort validation:** Validated at CLI level (30000-32767) before reaching provider\n9. **Environment variable fallback:** AgentCube provider falls back to `os.environ.get(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")` and `os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")` if not in metadata\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-022/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","time":{"start":1775854164950,"end":1775854164971}}}}
